6ï¸âƒ£ SQL Queries (Examples)
1. Sales Aggregation
SELECT 
    Variant,
    SUM(Sales) AS Total_Revenue,
    SUM(Units_Sold) AS Total_Units
FROM sales_data
GROUP BY Variant;

2. Region-wise Grouping
SELECT 
    Region,
    SUM(Units_Sold) AS Units_Sold,
    SUM(Sales) AS Revenue
FROM sales_data
GROUP BY Region;

3. Variant Comparison Query
SELECT 
    Variant,
    AVG(Engine_HP) AS Avg_HP,
    AVG(Sales) AS Avg_Sales
FROM car_specs
GROUP BY Variant;

7ï¸âƒ£ Snowflake Setup Instructions
1. Create Warehouse
CREATE WAREHOUSE mustang_wh 
WITH WAREHOUSE_SIZE='XSMALL' 
AUTO_SUSPEND=300 
AUTO_RESUME=TRUE;

2. Create Database & Schema
CREATE DATABASE mustang_db;
CREATE SCHEMA analytics;

3. Upload Dataset

Use Snowflake Web UI â†’ Load Data
OR
Use command line PUT commands to load CSVs.

4. Connect Snowflake to Power BI

Open Power BI Desktop

Select Get Data â†’ Snowflake

Enter:

Server Name

Warehouse

Role

Database

Choose Import or DirectQuery

8ï¸âƒ£ How to Use the Dashboard

Open the .pbix file in Power BI Desktop.

Use the navigation menu to switch between pages.

Apply filters for:

Region

Variant

Customer segment

Dealer

Hover over visuals for tooltips.

Click charts to activate cross-filtering.

Use drill-through pages for deeper insights.

